                            <span class="step-card-label">Step Two</span>
                            <h3>Prepare the Mounting Surface</h3>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <p>Preparation varies depending on the surface material. Use the guide below to determine the right approach for your installation.</p>
                        <div class="surface-grid">
                            <div class="surface-card">
                                <strong>Wood or Siding</strong>
                                <p>Use the included wood screws. Drill pilot holes to prevent splitting.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="surface-card">
                                <strong>Masonry, Brick, or Concrete</strong>
                                <p>Use a masonry drill bit. Insert wall anchors or masonry screws (not included).</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="surface-card">
                                <strong>Other Surfaces</strong>
                                <p>Consult a hardware store for compatible screws or anchors for your surface type.</p>
